cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with top-k maximum inner product search, which is a fundamental task in information retrieval and recommender systems. It also involves sampling algorithms, which are commonly used in IR. 

It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as top-k MIPS is a central task in many machine learning applications. 

The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category is also a possibility as the paper proposes algorithmic engineering techniques to deploy wedge sampling on budgeted top-k MIPS. 

The Database (cs.DB) category is another possibility as the paper deals with retrieving top-k results from a large dataset. 

Finally, the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category is a possibility as top-k MIPS is used in image retrieval and object recognition tasks.
